methods.name: ReadOnlyDeserializer
methods.logic: Constructor for the ReadOnlyDeserializer class. Likely initializes the deserializer with the provided isolate, snapshot data, and a flag indicating whether rehashing is allowed.

methods.name: DeserializeIntoIsolate
methods.logic: Deserializes the read-only blob from the snapshot data into the given isolate. This process reconstructs objects and data in the isolate's read-only memory space.

methods.name: PostProcessNewObjects
methods.logic: Performs any necessary post-processing on the newly deserialized objects. This might involve setting up internal pointers or performing other initialization tasks specific to the read-only objects.
